<br>
Basically, its smooth sailing down to the entrance to the Royal's area.  This is where it starts getting hard.<br>
<br>
You want an FD puller.  Monk is preferable, but an SK can work.  I dont suggest a Necro due to low AC, damage mitigation, and lower hps generally.  Although I've seen it done.  There is also a trap right before the door that will do some damage and &quot;stun&quot; you for a bit.  Try to disarm this prior to going in.<br>
 <br>
A level 60 enchanter can mez most mobs in this area.  A 56 one can probably as well, although resists will be higher.  I wouldnt suggest trying with less.  If I recall 55 and under was pretty much a death sentence as the mob would resist mez almost all the time.  They are also charmable generally.<br>
<br>
Some mobs will be unmezable if I recall.  But you should be able to charm those if there are any.<br>
<br>
This is where discipline is really important.  There is a fast respawn here.  Around 15 minutes.  This means you need to clear the area around the &quot;moat&quot; and inside in under that time frame, or you'll just end up spinning your wheels.<br>
<br>
Depending on your force and how well your enchanter can mez and how well people listen, you can also just charge the door.  This is generally what we do these days, rather than clear.   But its risky as you'll have about 11 mobs on you at once.  You'll need fast DPS, good discipline with people using assist religiously.  One broken mez can wipe you out from this point on.<br>
<br>
Snare is godly.<br>
<br>
Snare everything.<br>
<br>
One running mob here will also wipe you out.  And they run pretty fast.<br>
<br>
Once your inside, you go left at the first turn.  Its actually a square that just goes completely around, but by going left you can pull a lot more easily without risking pulling the Prince by mistake.<br>
<br>
There is a little room to the left where you can setup.  From here you can send you monk out to pull the other areas.<br>
<br>
If you want to move to the Prince, one the way is clear, you can move up past the door to the Overking/Queen.  There is another room where you can buff up.  Then to the left again is the door to the Prince.  There are about 8-11 mobs in there if I recall.  This is again where you use a rogue and monk to pull the room, hopefully singlely.  Once his guards are mostly dead, you can charge the room.<br>
<br>
Remember, we're talking 15 minute respawns here, so you have to be fast.  15 minutes sounds like a lot of time, but it really isnt.<br>
<br>
After that (or assuming you dont want to risk it, there is a high probability of wipeout here if your not careful or havent done it before.) you can go back to the other door and pull the entrance to the library.  Once the entrance is pulled, you can move everyone in, and your monk can pull the library itself.<br>
<br>
Remember, you need a rogue here to open the door.  Once you pass this point, a wipeout means that you'll have to summon corpses at the zone really.  Unless you have a rogue who has the right faction to get in.<br>
<br>
Once you clear the library you can move on down into it.  Just jump on down.  Again, you can setup in the corner opposite the stairs and pull the room beyond it.<br>
<br>
This is where it becomes tricky.<br>
<br>
Just through the door is a short hallway with raised platforms on both sides.  The first couple of steps are okay, then you hit a PIT TRAP that will drop you down into the Overking room.  Make sure everyone has lev and invis up here.  Invis wont help much, but it should help to lower aggro radius a bit just in case.  Also make sure all bard songs are OFF.  If you have a bard or two, absolutely make sure they are not singing here.<br>
<br>
You'll probably lose one or two people to that trap.  It always happens.  If it does, just let them die, and either summon their corpse, or tell them to wait.<br>
<br>
Once your through, if all the mobs here have been cleared you can head down into the secret hall.  If they havent been, then you can quickly run up onto the left or right platform (make sure you tell everyone which one your using in advance) and kill the mobs there.  There are about 8 or so mobs here.  Again, do it fast.<br>
<br>
Once the mobs are dead, you'll want to move into the secret tunnel.  You go back down into the hallway that contains the pit trap, and keep going into the opposite wall from the door in.  From there you'll enter a hallway.  It goes forward a bit, then turns right.<br>
<br>
This is important.  You'll want to go all the way, turn right and go down the hallway a bit.  Everyone MUST be past the corner or they'll aggro the previous room mobs as they respawn.  There's a couple of wanderers there that'll &quot;see&quot; you through the fake wall if your not all the way down.<br>
<br>
There are also several wanderers in the hall, but they're generally easy to take care of.<br>
<br>
After you kill them, you'll want to start to buff if necessary.  Circle of Seasons is every important or Circle of Winter at the very least as the Overking proc's an AE fire attack.  Does serious DoT damage equal or worse than Talendor.  We're talking around 1100points if I recall.  If your are not 55+ with an FR of at least 150-200 buffed...you will die.  Its simply a question of how long.<br>
<br>
Now there are several ways to pull the King room.<br>
<br>
First you can get a monk to pull them out.  The King room is down the corridor, and is the first door on your RIGHT.  If you open the door straight down you'll enter the Queen room and you will wipe your raid out.  Make sure you know where your going at this point.<br>
<br>
Keep the raid about halfway down the hallway after that initual right turn.  This has to be done quickly or you'll end up with respawns along with the King.<br>
<br>
Now you can have a monk try to split the guards and chain pull them up.  This takes luck and timing as a bad chain will pull everything.  If that happens, everyone should be on the overking and try to take him out, and have the cleric loot before everyone dies.<br>
<br>
The second method is to simply charge the room and have the enchanters try to mez most of the mobs there.  That isnt all that effective due to the Overking's DoT, but if you keep him inside his pit, then it should be okay.<br>
<br>
The Third way involves sending in a monk to pull the overking into the hallway, then having a non-KoS person hail the king to keep him in place till his guards head on back.<br>
<br>
I mention this only because I'm sure someone else will.  This is considered an exploit and is a bannable offense by SoE and could result in both the banning and suspension of the people involved (ie the raid) as well as the disbanding of the involved guilds.<br>
<br>
I really dont suggest this method.<br>
<br>
Thats really it.  I highly suggest keeping a 58+ Necro who can use tiny coffins on tap.  There are weird aggro issues from the library on, where I've seen raids aggro the overking even though no one was even close.  The chance of a total wipeout from a first time raid is very high.  If odd aggro happens and you get 20 or so mobs past the rogue only door, you chould try to camp a cleric or two out, but I've never seen this work.  Once the cleric gets back on and starts rezing, they cant keep up with the mob respawn and eventually everyone dies again.<br>
<br>
This is definitely one of those raids where the fewer you have the better, so long as they are top notch and mostly 60.<br>
<br>
You can do it with a force between 53-58....but its much more difficult.<br>
<br>
Anyway, this is just a simple guide.  I highly suggest checking the web and the cleric boards for more detailed guides.  There are many other things you need to look out for really.<br>
